column177:
04/Nov/24 1:09 AM;712020:40fd23e0-93b6-4cd1-83b8-a9a3a0591301;{quote}why don’t we fix the SQL in this state?{quote}

All of these, when reported, are “final state” states. There are various internal self-validation attempts, so if/when we reach INVALID_SQL_BAD_SYNTAX, it’s after retrying multiple times

This one should be rare as indeed in the vast majority of cases the LLM will be able to self-correct syntax
